$interpreted: : A few days later...
Hyacinthus: Eve...will she be alright?
Nigel: What's that noise? Are the nobles' men here to get Eve?
Nigel: Eve, I'll be right back. Cin, take care of Eve for me!
Hyacinthus: Eve, please tell me you'll be fine...
Hyacinthus: Who are you!?
Aosta: Member of the Feather Clan, is that her?
Hyacinthus: Are you here to harm Eve...? Get out!
Eve: Don't come near me...*sob*...!
Eve: You're... healing me? But, why... ?
Aosta: As a member of the precious Feather Clan, you don't have the right to die.
Eve: That person...what does he want from me?
Aosta: I don't know. However, what I do know is that your identity as a member of the Feather Clan will attract more danger to you and those around you.
Eve: Does that include...people I care about?
Aosta: Yes.
Eve: I don't want...something like that to happen.
Aosta: That depends on the decision you make.
Eve: What's your name?
Aosta: Aosta Clovis.
Eve: Aosta, you only helped me because I am a member of the Feather Clan...am I right?
Aosta: Yes.
Eve: I see, but still...Th-Thank you...
Nigel: Get away from her, NOW!
Aosta: Hey...
Eve: Stop it!
Eve: N...Nigel, are you okay?
Nigel: I'm fine, Eve, did he do anything to you?
Eve: He's not a hitman sent by the nobles.
Nigel: B-But didn't he just...
Eve: Nigel, I must leave with him.
Nigel: Why?
Eve: As an awakened member of the Feather Clan...my identity will attract unwanted attention. For the sake of the children...I-I cannot stay here...
Aosta: Your troubled look is an eyesore. Stop it.
Eve: I'm sorry. I was just...
Aosta: I have no interest in what's on your mind. As a side note, I'm quite impressed that you trusted me so easily.
Eve: ...It just happens that I want to leave the Slums and you just happen to need a member of the Feather Clan.
Eve: We take advantage of each other...that's our relationship, isn't it?
Aosta: Yes.
Eve: On top of that, you...don't seem like a bad person.
Aosta: ...Hmph. So your name's Eve? Let's get moving.
Eve: Give me a new name. The name "Eve" will remind me of the Slums.
Aosta: Then from now on, I shall call you Yamitsuki.
Eve: Yamitsuki? Is there a meaning behind this name?
Aosta: No idea. It just rolls off the tongue. If you don't like it, come up with one yourself.
Aosta: I don't want to waste time on petty things like this.
Yamitsuki: Yamitsuki...not bad.
